        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_aǧ0yjyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aǧ˳yjyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>aǧ˳yd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>aǧujun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth> aǧud</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>повадиться</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>get the habit</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>капризничать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>be capricious</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>беситься</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>madden</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aǧ˳yd</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>aǧud</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>бешеный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>mad</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>īw bīræǧ næ fosyl saǧ˳ydi</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>один волк повадился (ходить) к нашему стаду</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>one wolf got into the habit of (walking) to our herd</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>zærbatgutæ isaǧudæncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ласточки пришли в смятение</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the swallows got mad</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 13</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>aǧ˳yd kujtaw mæm læbūrync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>они кидаются на меня, как бешеные собаки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they rush at me like mad dogs</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Niger"
                            /><biblScope>134</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>aǧud beræǧtaw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>как бешеные волки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>like mad wolves</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"
                            /><biblScope>286%l3%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>dengiz aǧudaw læburdta nawtæmæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>море, как бешеное, кидалось на корабли</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the sea, as if it was mad, threw itself on the ships</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><biblScope>Geografi I 62</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>aǧud kuji komi finkæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пена изо рта бешеной собаки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>foam from the mouth of a mad dog</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1936 I
                            67</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Корень *%igu-%i, сращенный с превербом %ia-%i; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>gū(jū-, zū-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>gū-(jū-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>идти</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>спешить</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>А.
                            Fгеimаn</author><biblScope>Rocznik Orjentalistyczny, 3, 1927, стр.
                            161</biblScope></bibl>).%r1%r Осетинский отражает здесь старую
                    непалатали зованную форму %igu-%i, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>-gu</w></mentioned> во второй части сложных слов: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vanar-gu</w>
                        <gloss><q>бродящий по лесу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>agre-gu</w>
                        <gloss><q>идущий в голове</q></gloss></mentioned> и т. п. Та же основа,
                    сращенная с превербом %iīv%i | %iev%i-, налична еще в одном осетинском глаголе:
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/> I %ievǧujun%i ‘миновать’ q. v.
                    Сюда же <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zyd"/> | %izud%i ‘жадный’.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The root *%igu-%i combined with the preverb %ia-%i; cf.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>gū(jū-, zū-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>gū-(jū-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>go</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>hurry</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>А.
                            Fгеimаn</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Rocznik Orjentalistyczny, 3,
                            1927, стр. 161</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Rocznik
                            Orjentalistyczny, 3, 1927, p. 161</biblScope></bibl>).%r1%r Ossetic
                    displays here an old unpalatalized form %igu-%i, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>-gu</w></mentioned> in the second part of compounds: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vanar-gu</w>
                        <gloss><q>wandering through the woods</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w>agre-gu</w>
                        <gloss><q>going ahead</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. The same stem combined
                    with the preverb %iīv%i | %iev%i- is found in another one Ossetic verb: <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/> I %ievǧujun%i ‘escape’ q. v. Also see
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zyd"/> | %izud%i ‘greedy’.</etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Сопоставление с <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>%r3%r gav</w>
                        <gloss><q>кричащий</q></gloss></mentioned> менее убедительно, ср. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/>.</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">The comparison with <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>%r3%r gav</w>
                        <gloss><q>crying</q></gloss></mentioned> is less convincing, cf. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/>.</note>
            </entry>
